About six kids are said to have died while trying to escape from bandits attack in Kasai village of Batseri local government area of Katsina State. The children, who according to information died when being scurried out by their mothers to escape from bandits’ attack drowned in a dam during heavy rainfall in the village late Friday. However, the bandits had attacked the residence of one businessman named Alhaji Yunusa Rugabza where they killed him instantly. Eye witness account said that there was sporadic gunshots which followed by  heavy rainfall, leading to the mass escape of villagers, adding that it also led to unfortunate mishap as nine women ran into a dam with some children where they drowned. The district head of Batsari, Tukur Muazu Rumah who confirmed the incident said the fleeing women fell into the dam with their children, and six children aged between five and seven years died in the dam.